<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="117" MadCap:lastWidth="1219">
    <body>
        <p>The background changes from one color to another. Click the down arrow to open a small window. In this window, click the down arrow next to the <span class="Emphasis">Start</span> field and select a color to use at the beginning of the gradient. Then click the down arrow next to the <span class="Emphasis">End</span> field and select the color to use at the end of the gradient. Finally, click the down arrow next to the <span class="Emphasis">Style</span> field and select a direction for the gradient effect or choose "solid." Click <span class="Emphasis">OK</span> to accept the settings. When you click off the properties field, a small icon is displayed in the field, showing how the effect will look. If you are change the color for a style item that also has a gradient, the gradient properties have precedence over the solid color.</p>
    </body>
</html>